}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \par
}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab }{\plain \fs24 \b\f1 90-93.}{\plain \fs24 \f1   Ulysses' speech begins, like classical epic, }{\plain \fs24 \i\f1 in medias res}{\plain \fs24 \f1  (in the midst of the action, \softline
i.e., not at its beginning).  Dante would seem to be portraying him as the author of his own self-celebrating song, a 'mini-epic,' as it were.  He makes it sound as though staying with Circe, the \softline
